  "text": "We model a network as an undirected graph G(V, E), where V is the set of network nodes and E is the set of links (or edges)-in [CITATION_1] , we extend our analysis to directed graphs as well. We use the terms network and graph interchangeably. We assume that G is connected (there exists a path from any node to any other node) and that all routes are simple (acyclic). Finally, we say that two physical paths between a pair of nodes are distinct, if they differ in even one of the edges traversed.",
